text: Spoštovani , prosim , da zasedete svoja mesta .
translation: Dears, please take your seats.
translation_added_spaces: Dears , please take your seats .
new_translations: Dears , please take your seats .

text: V naši sredini pozdravljam predsednika države , gospoda Boruta Pahorja in predsednika Državnega zbora , gospoda Janka Vebra .
translation: In our midst, I welcome the President of the State, Mr Borut Pahor and the President of the National Assembly, Mr Janko Veber.
translation_added_spaces: In our midst , I welcome the President of the State , Mr Borut Pahor and the President of the National Assembly , Mr Janko Veber .
new_translations: In our midst , I welcome the President of the State , Mr Borut Pahor and the President of the National Assembly , Mr Janko Veber .

text: Lepo pozdravljena .
translation: Well, hello there.
translation_added_spaces: Well , hello there .
new_translations: Well , hello there .

text: Besedo dajem spoštovanemu predsedniku Državnega zbora , gospodu Janku Vebru .
translation: I give the Word to the Honorable President of the National Assembly, Mr Janko Vebr.
translation_added_spaces: I give the Word to the Honorable President of the National Assembly , Mr Janko Vebr .
new_translations: I give the Word to the Honorable President of the National Assembly , Mr Janko Veber .

text: Izvolite , prosim .
translation: Here you go, please.
translation_added_spaces: Here you go , please .
new_translations: Here you go , please .

text: Hvala za besedo , predsedujoča .
translation: Thank you for your word, Chairman.
translation_added_spaces: Thank you for your word , Chairman .
new_translations: Thank you for your word , Chairman .

text: Spoštovani predsednik Republike Slovenije , gospod Borut Pahor , spoštovani poslanke in poslanci , gospe in gospodje !
translation: Dear President of the Republic of Slovenia, Mr Borut Pahor, honourable Members, ladies and gentlemen!
translation_added_spaces: Dear President of the Republic of Slovenia , Mr Borut Pahor , honourable Members , ladies and gentlemen !
new_translations: Dear President of the Republic of Slovenia , Mr Borut Pahor , honourable Members , ladies and gentlemen !

text: Dovolite mi , da vas nagovorim ob izteku VI. mandata Državnega zbora .
translation: Allow me to address you at the expiry of VI. the term of office of the National Assembly.
translation_added_spaces: Allow me to address you at the expiry of VI . the term of office of the National Assembly .
new_translations: Allow me to address you at the expiry of VI . the term of office of the National Assembly .

text: Mandat se izteka prej , kot določa Ustava , kar govori o tem , da smo delovali v zelo zahtevnih razmerah , ki so jih v veliki meri narekovale tako gospodarske in finančne razmere , ki pa so nastale v svetu , ne v Sloveniji , to moramo poudariti , seveda pa smo sestavni del tega dogajanja bili tudi v Sloveniji .
translation: The mandate expires earlier than the Constitution states, which speaks of how we acted in very difficult situations, which were largely referred to by both economic and financial conditions, which were created in the world, not in Slovenia, which we must stress and, of course, we were an integral part of this event in Slovenia.
translation_added_spaces: The mandate expires earlier than the Constitution states , which speaks of how we acted in very difficult situations , which were largely referred to by both economic and financial conditions , which were created in the world , not in Slovenia , which we must stress and , of course , we were an integral part of this event in Slovenia .
new_translations: The mandate expires earlier than the Constitution states , which speaks of how we acted in very difficult situations , which were largely referred to by both economic and financial conditions , which were created in the world , not in Slovenia , which we must stress and , of course , we were an integral part of this event in Slovenia .

text: In ukrepi , ki jih je bilo treba sprejemati v Državnem zboru , so bili zelo pomembni , da smo lahko obvladovali ravno to področje .
translation: And the measures that had to be taken at the National Assembly were very important that we could manage this very area.
translation_added_spaces: And the measures that had to be taken at the National Assembly were very important that we could manage this very area .
new_translations: And the measures that had to be taken at the National Assembly were very important that we could manage this very area .

text: Dosegli smo soglasje tako med opozicijo in koalicijo , zato da smo lahko spremenili v dveh bistvenih točkah tudi Ustavo Republike Slovenije in tudi na mednarodnem področju sprejeli pomembno odločitev , ko smo soglasno ratificirali vstop Republike Hrvaške v Evropsko unijo .
translation: We reached agreement both between the opposition and the coalition, so that we could change the Constitution of the Republic of Slovenia in two essential points and also in the international field, when we unanimously ratified the accession of the Republic of Croatia to the European Union.
translation_added_spaces: We reached agreement both between the opposition and the coalition , so that we could change the Constitution of the Republic of Slovenia in two essential points and also in the international field , when we unanimously ratified the accession of the Republic of Croatia to the European Union .
new_translations: We reached agreement both between the opposition and the coalition , so that we could change the Constitution of the Republic of Slovenia in two essential points and also in the international field , when we unanimously ratified the accession of the Republic of Croatia to the European Union .

text: Zahvaljujem se spoštovanemu gospodu Janku Vebru , predsedniku Državnega zbora , za izrečene besede .
translation: I thank Mr Janko Vebr, President of the National Assembly, for the words spoken.
translation_added_spaces: I thank Mr Janko Vebr , President of the National Assembly , for the words spoken .
new_translations: I thank Mr Janko Veber , President of the National Assembly , for the words spoken .

text: Hvala lepa .
translation: Thank you very much.
translation_added_spaces: Thank you very much .
new_translations: Thank you very much .

text: Začenjam 1. sejo Državnega zbora , ki jo je na podlagi 81. člena Ustave Republike Slovenije sklical predsednik Republike Slovenije , gospod Borut Pahor , ki bo Državni zbor zdaj tudi nagovoril .
translation: I am starting the 1st meeting of the National Assembly, which was convened by the President of the Republic of Slovenia, Mr Borut Pahor, who will now address the State Assembly.
translation_added_spaces: I am starting the 1st meeting of the National Assembly , which was convened by the President of the Republic of Slovenia , Mr Borut Pahor , who will now address the State Assembly .
new_translations: I am starting the 1st meeting of the National Assembly , which was convened by the President of the Republic of Slovenia , Mr Borut Pahor , who will now address the State Assembly .

text: Prosim , spoštovani predsednik .
translation: Please, Your Honor.
translation_added_spaces: Please , Your Honor .
new_translations: Please , Your Honor .

text: Spoštovana gospa predsedujoča , spoštovane poslanke , spoštovani poslanci !
translation: Honored Madam Chairman, Honorable Members!
translation_added_spaces: Honored Madam Chairman , Honorable Members !
new_translations: Honored Madam Chairman , Honorable Members !

text: Sprejmite najprej , prosim , moje iskrene čestitke za vašo izvolitev .
translation: Accept first, please, my sincere congratulations for your election.
translation_added_spaces: Accept first , please , my sincere congratulations for your election .
new_translations: Accept first , please , my sincere congratulations for your election .

text: Po običaju bi zdaj moral najbrž dodati željo , da se skupaj potrudimo po svojih najboljših močeh .
translation: As usual, we should probably add to our desire to do our best together.
translation_added_spaces: As usual , we should probably add to our desire to do our best together .
new_translations: As usual , we should probably add to our desire to do our best together .

text: Ampak , že dolgo časa ni več ta čas običajen , zato mi pride na misel Churchill .
translation: But it's been a long time since this time is normal, so it comes to my mind, Churchill.
translation_added_spaces: But it's been a long time since this time is normal , so it comes to my mind , Churchill .
new_translations: But it's been a long time since this time is normal , so it comes to my mind , Churchill .

text: Trud po naših najboljših močeh ni več dovolj .
translation: Our best efforts are no longer enough.
translation_added_spaces: Our best efforts are no longer enough .
new_translations: Our best efforts are no longer enough .

text: Čas je , da naredimo pravo stvar .
translation: It's time to do the right thing.
translation_added_spaces: It's time to do the right thing .
new_translations: It's time to do the right thing .

text: Predsedniku republike , spoštovanemu gospodu Borutu Pahorju , se zahvaljujem za njegove besede in hvala gospod predsednik , da ste počastili Državni zbor s svojo prisotnostjo .
translation: I would like to thank Mr Borut Pahor for his words and thank Mr President for honoring the State Assembly with your presence.
translation_added_spaces: I would like to thank Mr Borut Pahor for his words and thank Mr President for honoring the State Assembly with your presence .
new_translations: I would like to thank Mr Borut Pahor for his words and thank Mr President for honoring the State Assembly with your presence .

text: Hvala lepa .
translation: Thank you very much.
translation_added_spaces: Thank you very much .
new_translations: Thank you very much .

text: Obveščena sem , da se današnje seje ne more udeležiti poslanec gospod Luka Mesec .
translation: I am informed that today's meeting cannot be attended by MEP Mr Luka Moon.
translation_added_spaces: I am informed that today's meeting cannot be attended by MEP Mr Luka Moon .
new_translations: I am informed that today's meeting cannot be attended by MEP Mr Luka Mesec .

text: Na sejo Državnega zbora sta vabljena predsednik Državne volilne komisije Anton Gašper Frantar in direktor Službe državne volilne komisije Dušan Vučko , in sicer k 2. točki dnevnega reda .
translation: At the meeting of the National Assembly, the President of the National Election Commission Anton Gasper Frantar and the Director of the Office of the National Election Commission Dusan Vuko are invited, to item 2 of the agenda.
translation_added_spaces: At the meeting of the National Assembly , the President of the National Election Commission Anton Gasper Frantar and the Director of the Office of the National Election Commission Dusan Vuko are invited , to item 2 of the agenda .
new_translations: At the meeting of the National Assembly , the President of the National Election Commission Anton Gašper Frantar and the Director of the Office of the National Election Commission Dušan Vučko are invited , to item 2 of the agenda .

text: Vse prisotne še enkrat lepo pozdravljam !
translation: I welcome everyone here again!
translation_added_spaces: I welcome everyone here again !
new_translations: I welcome everyone here again !

text: Pri vodenju seje Državnega zbora mi bosta pomagali generalna sekretarka državnega zbora , gospa Mojca Prelesnik , in namestnica generalne sekretarke , gospa Jerneja Bergoč .
translation: I will be assisted by the Secretary General of the National Assembly, Mrs Mojca Prelesnik, and the Deputy Secretary-General, Mrs Jerneja Bergoc.
translation_added_spaces: I will be assisted by the Secretary General of the National Assembly , Mrs Mojca Prelesnik , and the Deputy Secretary-General , Mrs Jerneja Bergoc .
new_translations: I will be assisted by the Secretary General of the National Assembly , Mrs Mojca Prelesnik , and the Deputy Secretary-General , Mrs Jerneja Bergoč .

text: Prehajamo na določitev dnevnega reda prve seje Državnega zbora .
translation: We are moving to set the agenda for the first meeting of the National Assembly.
translation_added_spaces: We are moving to set the agenda for the first meeting of the National Assembly .
new_translations: We are moving to set the agenda for the first meeting of the National Assembly .

text: Zahvaljujem se spoštovanemu dr. Miru Cerarju za podano obrazložitev predloga kandidata za predsednika Državnega zbora .
translation: I would like to thank Dr Mir Cerar for the proposed candidate for President of the National Assembly.
translation_added_spaces: I would like to thank Dr Mir Cerar for the proposed candidate for President of the National Assembly .
new_translations: I would like to thank Dr Mir Cerar for the proposed candidate for President of the National Assembly .

text: Besedo dajem predstavnikom poslanskih skupin za predstavitev stališč .
translation: I shall give the text to the representatives of the groups of Members for the presentation of their views.
translation_added_spaces: I shall give the text to the representatives of the groups of Members for the presentation of their views .
new_translations: I shall give the text to the representatives of the groups of Members for the presentation of their views .

text: Besedo ima Poslanska skupina DeSUS , gospod Karl Viktor Erjavec .
translation: The text is given by the DeSUS Group, Mr. Karl Viktor Erjavec.
translation_added_spaces: The text is given by the DeSUS Group , Mr . Karl Viktor Erjavec .
new_translations: The text is given by the DeSUS Group , Mr . Karl Viktor Erjavec .

text: Hvala lepa .
translation: Thank you very much.
translation_added_spaces: Thank you very much .
new_translations: Thank you very much .

text: Najprej bi se zahvalil predsedujoči gospe Marjani Kotnik Poropat za odlično vodenje te seje .
translation: First of all, I would like to thank President-in-Office Marjani Kotnik Poropat for the excellent conduct of this meeting.
translation_added_spaces: First of all , I would like to thank President-in-Office Marjani Kotnik Poropat for the excellent conduct of this meeting .
new_translations: First of all , I would like to thank President-in-Office Marjana Kotnik Poropat for the excellent conduct of this meeting .

text: Čestitam .
translation: Congratulations.
translation_added_spaces: Congratulations .
new_translations: Congratulations .

text: Čestitam seveda tudi vsem poslankam in poslancem na izvolitev in na potrditev mandata .
translation: Congratulations, of course, also to all Members and Members, on the election and on the approval of the mandate.
translation_added_spaces: Congratulations , of course , also to all Members and Members , on the election and on the approval of the mandate .
new_translations: Congratulations , of course , also to all Members and Members , on the election and on the approval of the mandate .

text: V stranki DeSUS bomo kandidaturo dr. Milana Brgleza za predsednika Državnega zbora podprli .
translation: In the Desus party, we will support Dr Milan Brglez's candidacy as President of the National Assembly.
translation_added_spaces: In the Desus party , we will support Dr Milan Brglez's candidacy as President of the National Assembly .
new_translations: In the Desus party , we will support Dr Milan Brglez candidacy as President of the National Assembly .

text: Podprli jo bomo zato , ker je nujno , da se Državni zbor čim prej konstituira in da čim prej pridemo tudi do vlade .
translation: We will support it because it is essential that the National Assembly be established as soon as possible and that we reach the government as soon as possible.
translation_added_spaces: We will support it because it is essential that the National Assembly be established as soon as possible and that we reach the government as soon as possible .
new_translations: We will support it because it is essential that the National Assembly be established as soon as possible and that we reach the government as soon as possible .

text: Vemo , kakšna je situacija v državi , in ključno za reševanje problemov , s katerimi se sooča Slovenija , je stabilna politična situacija .
translation: We know the situation in the country and the key to solving the problems facing Slovenia is a stable political situation.
translation_added_spaces: We know the situation in the country and the key to solving the problems facing Slovenia is a stable political situation .
new_translations: We know the situation in the country and the key to solving the problems facing Slovenia is a stable political situation .

text: Hvala lepa .
translation: Thank you very much.
translation_added_spaces: Thank you very much .
new_translations: Thank you very much .

text: Besedo ima Poslanska skupina Nova Slovenija – krščanski demokrati .
translation: The text is given by the Nova Slovenija Group – Christian Democrats.
translation_added_spaces: The text is given by the Nova Slovenija Group – Christian Democrats .
new_translations: The text is given by the Nova Slovenija Group – Christian Democrats .

text: Spoštovana gospa Ljudmila Novak , izvolite .
translation: Dear Lady Lyudmila Novak, please.
translation_added_spaces: Dear Lady Lyudmila Novak , please .
new_translations: Dear Lady Ljudmila Novak , please .
